# Project Setup and Configuration

This document outlines the project setup and configuration for TaskBuddy, a React and Redux-based task management application. It details how dependencies are managed, the project is structured, and how to get the application running.

## Overview

TaskBuddy is a feature-rich task management application developed for the JdeRobot GSoC 2025 React Challenge. It builds upon a standard task manager by incorporating advanced functionalities such as filtering, categorization, priority setting, search, drag-and-drop reordering, and due date management with notifications.

The application is live and accessible at: [https://taskbuddy-ztf4.onrender.com/](https://taskbuddy-ztf4.onrender.com/)

## Repository Structure

The project follows a well-organized structure to promote maintainability and scalability:

```
├── react_challenge
    ├── public
    │   └── index.html                   # HTML entry point
    ├── src
    │   ├── index.js                     # JavaScript entry point
    │   ├── components
    │   │   ├── App.jsx                  # Main app component
    │   │   ├── common
    │   │   │   ├── CategoryBadge.jsx    # Displays task category
    │   │   │   ├── EmptyState.jsx       # Empty state UI
    │   │   │   ├── HelpGuide.jsx        # Interactive help modal
    │   │   │   ├── LocalStorage.jsx     # Local storage interactions
    │   │   │   ├── PriorityBadge.jsx    # Displays task priority
    │   │   │   └── SearchBar.jsx        # Search input component
    │   │   ├── layout
    │   │   │   ├── Footer.jsx           # Footer component
    │   │   │   ├── Header.jsx           # Header component
    │   │   │   └── Layout.jsx           # Main layout component
    │   │   └── tasks
    │   │       ├── TaskCard.jsx         # Individual task display component
    │   │       ├── TaskFilter.jsx       # Task filtering controls
    │   │       ├── TaskForm.jsx         # Task creation form component
    │   │       └── TaskList.jsx         # Draggable task list component
    │   ├── redux
    │   │   ├── store.js                 # Redux store configuration
    │   │   ├── actions
    │   │   │   ├── categoryActions.jsx  # Actions for category management
    │   │   │   ├── filterActions.jsx    # Actions for filtering tasks
    │   │   │   └── taskActions.jsx      # Actions for task management
    │   │   └── reducers
    │   │       ├── categoryReducer.jsx  # Reducer for category state
    │   │       ├── filterReducer.jsx    # Reducer for filter state
    │   │       ├── index.jsx            # Root reducer combining all reducers
    │   │       └── taskReducer.jsx      # Reducer for task state
    │   └── styles
```

## Dependency Management

TaskBuddy utilizes npm (Node Package Manager) for managing project dependencies. The `package.json` file lists all the necessary libraries and their versions.

### `package.json`

This file defines the project's metadata, including its name, version, scripts, and dependencies.

[View `package.json` on GitHub](https://github.com/meekhumor/TaskBuddy/blob/main/package.json)

  "keywords": [],

The `dependencies` section lists the core libraries required for the application to function, including React for the UI, Redux for state management, `react-beautiful-dnd` and `react-dnd` for drag-and-drop functionality, and `date-fns` for date manipulation. `devDependencies` include tools for development and building such as Babel for transpilation, Webpack for bundling, and Tailwind CSS for styling.

### `package-lock.json`

This file records the exact versions of all dependencies, including transitive dependencies, ensuring consistent installations across different environments.

[View `package-lock.json` on GitHub](https://github.com/meekhumor/TaskBuddy/blob/main/package-lock.json)
